OL,3,CThe higher fines parents face as
OL,4,Cgovernment bids to boost school
OL,5,Cattendance
OL,7,FInstead the sanctions are meant for
OL,8,Funauthorised absences.
OL,10,FGeoff Barton, general secretary of the
OL,11,FAssociation of School and College
OL,12,FLeaders (ASCL), said: "However, it is
OL,13,Fimportant to understand that these
OL,14,Ffines predominately relate to pupils
OL,15,Fwho are taken out of school for term-
OL,16,Ftime holidays.
OL,18,F"While nobody wants to be in a
OL,19,Fposition of fining parents there
OL,20,Fsimply has to be a marker that this is
OL,21,Fnot acceptable.
